label.value: abnormal transcriptional response to amino acid starvation

value.value: A conjugation phenotype in which regulation of transcription in response to starvation for one or more amino acids is abnormal.

label.value: decreased translation of amino acid biosynthesis proteins during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of translation of one or more proteins involved in amino acid biosynthesis is decreased.

label.value: increased mitochondrial pre-mRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any unspliced or incompletely spliced mRNA precursor measured in the mitochondrion is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cleavage furrow during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cleavage furrow does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of protein localization from Golgi apparatus to cleavage furrow

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, localization of a protein from the Golgi apparatus to the cleavage furrow ring is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of histone H3 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of histone H3 acetylation is lower extent than normal.

label.value: altered histone H3 acetyltransferase substrate specificity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the substrate specificity of a gene product that executes histone H3 acetyltransferase activity is altered. For example, preference for modified (e.g. methylated) H3 molecules may be enhanced or diminished.

label.value: decreased methylated histone binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which methylated histone binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant occurs to a lower extent than normal. The affected protein may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with actin filaments that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased histone H3 acetyltransferase processivity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed processivity of a histone H3 acetyltransferase activity is lower than normal. Processivity refers to the number of methylation reactions catalyzed (methyl residues added) per histone binding event.

label.value: abnormal histone acetyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate or other catalytic property of a histone acetyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to meiotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle pole body and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to meiotic spindle during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle is abolished during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to meiotic spindle during meiosis II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle is abolished during the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to centromere central core during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the central core of the centromeric regions is abolished during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal histone modification

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects histone modification.

label.value: abnormal protein modification during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein modification is abnormal during the meiotic cell cycle. All modifications may be affected, or only modifications of a certain type, or on specific proteins, or even specific sites within specific proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at protein coding gene during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions containing protein-coding genes during the first meiotic nuclear division. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at telomere during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal in telomeric regions during the first meiotic nuclear division. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H2A phosphorylation at silent mating-type cassette during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which histone H2A phosphorylation occurs to a greater extent than normal at the silent mating-type cassette during the first meiotic nuclear division. All histone H2A phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on histone H2A may be increased.

label.value: abnormal mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor complex assembly is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal telomere length during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomere length is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal telomere organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal telomere morphology.

label.value: altered mature ncRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of mature non-coding RNA (ncRNA) measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total ncRNA or a specific ncRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mature ncRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature non-coding RNA (ncRNA) measured in a cell is lower than normal. Total ncRNA or a specific ncRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased mature ncRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature non-coding RNA (ncRNA) measured in a cell is higher than normal. Total ncRNA or a specific ncRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered mature rRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of mature ribosomal RNA (rRNA) measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total rRNA or a specific rRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal mature ncRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature non-coding RNA (ncRNA) measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total ncRNA or a specific ncRNA may be measured.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mature rRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature ribosomal RNA (rRNA) measured in a cell is lower than normal. Total rRNA or a specific rRNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased translation of amino acid biosynthesis proteins in response to amino acid starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of translation of one or more proteins involved in amino acid biosynthesis is decreased in response to starvation for one or more amino acids.

label.value: decreased transcription of amino acid biosynthesis genes in response to amino acid starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription of amino acid biosynthesis genes from RNA polymerase II promoters occurs to a lower extent than normal in response to starvation for one or more amino acids. Amino acid biosynthesis genes are those whose products are involved in amino acid biosynthetic processes.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to amino acid starvation

value.value: A gene expression phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of translation in response to starvation for one or more amino acids is abnormal.

label.value: mitotic spindle collapse

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short mitotic spindle assembles, and may begin elongation, but does not elongate normally or completely, and eventually collapses. Upon collapse the spindle may break or shrink.

label.value: premature mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the onset of anaphase of the mitotic cell cycle begins earlier than normal.

label.value: abnormal mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the metaphase/anaphase transition of the mitotic cell cycle is abnormal.

label.value: decreased mitotic cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading is decreased during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to double-stranded DNA, i.e. the leading strand, in chromatin.

label.value: abnormal cohesin loading

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cohesin loading is abnormal. Cohesin loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to chromatin.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with heterochromatin and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal cohesin loading

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cohesin loading is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Cohesin loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to chromatin.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with heterochromatin and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased mitotic cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is increased during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to single-stranded DNA, i.e. the lagging strand, in chromatin.

label.value: normal mitotic cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to single-stranded DNA, i.e. the lagging strand, in chromatin.

label.value: decreased mitotic cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is decreased during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin ssDNA (lagging strand) loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to single-stranded DNA, i.e. the lagging strand, in chromatin.

label.value: abolished mitotic cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading does not occur during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin dsDNA (leading strand) loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to double-stranded DNA of the leading strand in chromatin.

label.value: decreased cellular phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased cellular phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: normal cellular phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic M phase

value.value: A cell cycle phenotype in which the duration of M phase of the mitotic cell cycle is shorter than normal.

label.value: abnormal chitin synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of chitin synthase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished chitin synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which chitin synthase activity is absent.

label.value: increased chitin synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of chitin synthase activity is increased.

label.value: decreased rDNA copy number during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of ribosomal DNA (rDNA) repeats present in the rDNA arrays on chromosome III is significantly lower than the range in wild type cells.
